The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 CPM slams Bush letter

 New Delhi, Nov. 5: The CPM today faulted Manmohan Singh?s letter congratulating George W. Bush on his re-election as US President.

 The CPM said the government was not following the common minimum programme on foreign policy. It said the Prime Minister had written to Bush without considering what his policies would be. ?To state that the global war against terrorism benefited enormously from Bush?s steadfast resolve and leadership is contrary to all facts and evidence.? 




